  "texts": [
    "The vanishing gradient problem is the most pressing issue.",
    "As the size of the input series increases, the influence of things distant from the presently inputted item decreases exponentially, resulting in low performance for lengthy data like proteins and other big molecules (Hochreiter, 1998).",
    "Moreover, training time is proportional to sequence length since the same operation is performed many times.",
    "Even in cases where the elements in sequential data have intricate associations, the features of these elements are not effectively learned.",
    "To address this vanishing gradient problem (which prevents the weights from being updated), the theory of long short-term memory (LSTM) was developed years ago and recently adopted extensively (Yu et al., 2019)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
